31/01/19
MOTOR SUBSYSTEM: En route.
RADIO SUBSYSTEM: Completed.
POWER SUBSYSTEM: Pending completion.
ARDUINO SUBSYSTEM: Hardware complete, code pending completion.
3D PRINTING: Pending completion.
PCB: Pending completion.

GOALS: 
  3D print a pulley and test the motor.
  Put in electrical safety components such as 11V regulator for motor driver, external flyback diode on motor and fuses.
  Calculate total current required across each subsystem.
  
CHALLENGES:
  Can't calculate current until testing of motor is complete.
  Can't implement solenoid until testing is complete which also prevents calculation of total current.
  Need to solve for how the arduino will know where the monkey is at any one time.
  
NOTES:
  Best idea for 3rd challenge is to have a mechanical stop that the monkey triggers at which point the motor changes direction
  and continues to hoist the monkey until it is tripped again i.e. the pulley fully coils around twice.
  
  Website for designing a circuit with arduino: https://www.circuito.io/app?components=512,11021
  
THOUGHTS: 
  Maybe a rotational encoder would be beneficial to track the speed of the motor. An IR gateway as a failsafe to the
  mechanical trigger could be important too.

