23/06/19
MOTOR SUBSYSTEM: Completed.
RADIO SUBSYSTEM: Working on code.
POWER SUBSYSTEM: Reverse voltage protector arrived.
ARDUINO SUBSYSTEM: Regulator arrived and a battery can be useful to keep the Arduino on.
3D PRINTING: Will complete when PCB and props in place.
PCB: Pending completion.

NOTES:
  During calibration to find bottom of arc the motor should turn slowly to not overdraw current at the bottom or fall too quickly.
  It might be worth capping the motor's PWM to 75% so that it can't free fall per se. The reason for this is that when the motor speed
  changes from very fast to very fast in the opposite direction it draws a huge current.
  Key printed and placed but not Loctite'd in place yet.
  
