31/07/19
THE FIX FOR THE POWER SUPPLY DEPENDS ON THE TOTAL RESPONSE OF THE MOTOR! A sudden change of PWM duty cycle causes a spike in voltage
which overloads the PSU if the PWM is already near 100%. The fix is to keep the PWM at a threshold point where even the largest
spike has no effect.

Will implement fix when new Arduino Unos arrive.
